OL,3,CConsumer confidence 'collapses' as
OL,4,CMiddle East war escalates
OL,6,FMeanwhile, spending predictions rose
OL,7,Fseven points to 13 as shoppers
OL,8,Fexpected to see rising energy costs
OL,9,Freflected across the economy.
OL,11,FBRC chief executive Helen Dickinson
OL,12,Fsaid: "Consumer confidence collapsed
OL,13,Fas the Middle East conflict raised the
OL,14,Fprospect of higher inflation in the
OL,15,Fmonths ahead.
OL,17,F"As stock markets tumbled, confidence
OL,18,Fin both the economy and personal
OL,19,Ffinances dropped to their lowest
OL,20,Flevels on record.
OL,26,@tD@GOUyD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/4
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1774490589
OL,3,CConsumer confidence 'collapses' as
OL,4,CMiddle East war escalates
OL,6,F"The drop in confidence was most
OL,7,Fpronounced among the Boomer
OL,8,Fgeneration, who are most reliant on
OL,9,Finvestment and pension funds.
OL,11,FMs Dickinson added: "The current
OL,12,Fconflict has created a great deal of
OL,13,Funcertainty in the economy. Inflation
OL,14,Fis expected to rise in the coming
OL,15,Fmonths. Just as the economy was
OL,16,Fbeginning to turn a corner on
OL,17,Finflation, the rise in global energy
OL,18,Fprices is particularly unwelcome for
OL,19,Fbusinesses and families.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@UOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/4
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30704
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1774490589
OL,3,CConsumer confidence 'collapses' as
OL,4,CMiddle East war escalates
OL,6,F"It is now vitally important that
OL,7,FGovernment policy does not exacerbate
OL,8,Fthe situation, and bringing down the
OL,9,Fcost of living must be a top priority.
OL,11,F"From new employment laws to rising
OL,12,Fpackaging taxes, Government must focus
OL,13,Fon how it can minimise unnecessary
OL,14,Fcosts to retailers, thereby helping
OL,15,Fprotect ordinary households from the
OL,16,Frising cost of living."
OL,18,FOpinium surveyed 2,000 UK adults
OL,19,Fbetween March 10-13.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@AOUxD@WO]
